SIMPLE: natter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Natter
<hw>Nat"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>knetta</ets> to grumble.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To find fault; to
be peevish.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. or Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To talk constantly; to chatter incessantly to
prattle; <as>as, <ex>nattering</ex> like a chatterbox</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Natterjack</ent>⟦br⟧
